tted to equipping our students with both knowledge and practical skills that meet industry expectations. At COCSIT, we strive to provide the best possible education by fostering an environment that encourages innovation, critical thinking, and lifelong learning. Our mission focuses on developing skilled human resources and enhancing the employability of our students through value-based education, hands-on training, and industry-oriented programs. We believe that education is not merely the accumulation of information but the transformation of an individual into a responsible and capable citizen. Guided by our motto, “Knowledge is liberation of mankind” (ऋते ज्ञानान्न मुक्ति: | श्रेष्ठ ज्ञानाशिवाय सुटका नाही.) , we aim to inspire our students to pursue excellence and contribute meaningfully to society. With a team of dedicated faculty, modern infrastructure, and a student-centric approach, we continuously endeavor to create opportunities that help our learners achieve their full potential. I invite all aspiring students to join us in this journey of knowledge, innovation, and success. Dr. R. S. Awasthi Principal College of Computer Science and Information Technology (COCSIT), Latur Administrative & Teaching Experience Total Experience: 39 Years Currently serving as the Principal of COCSIT, Latur. Previously served as the Principal of Shivaji Mahavidyalaya, Renapur, Dist. Latur. Principal, Badrinarayan Barwale College, Jalna from 24th June 2004 to 5th April 2011 Reader and Head, Microbiology Department in Rajarshi Shahu Mahavidyalaya, Latur from 1987 to 2004 Prestigious Awards & Honors Best Principal (Rural) Award (A.Y. 2020-2021) by Swami Ramanand Teerth Marathwada University, Nanded Recipient of "Dronacharya Puraskar-2003" given by Rashtriya Kala Gun Gaurav Pratisthan, Pune Research Fellow Award given by the American Biographical Institute (December 31, 2005), North Carolina, USA Honorary appointment to the "Research Board of Advisors" by American Biographical Institute from 2005 "Lifetime Achievement Award" by NIC New Delhi (January 02, 2007) UGC Research Projects i) Minor Research Project 'Single cell oil and gamma Linolenic acid production from TSP by oleaginous fungi' Sanctioned & Sponsored by UGC vide letter no. F.No. 23-246/98 (WRO) dated January 9, 1999 Status: Completed successfully ii) Major Research Project 'Potential research for production of Biosurfactant from plant material using microbial technology' Sanctioned & Sponsored by UGC vide letter no. F.No. 34-231/2008(SR) dated 29th December 2008 Status: Completed Patent: Indian Patent awarded in 2013 International Research Visits: Sri Lanka and Bhutan Research Accomplishments i) Ph.D. Research: Actively engaged research work for eight years. Thesis entitled "Studies on Microbial Production of Single Cell Oil" completed under the guidance of Dr. M.S. Andhale, Govt. Inst. of Science, Aurangabad ii) Published 22 Research papers iii) Presented 51 Research Papers iv) Guidance: 8 Ph.D. Students and 4 M.Phil. Students. Currently guiding 6 Ph.D. students and 1 M.Phil. Student v) Guidance: 14 students for research project work for partial fulfillment of B.Sc. degree vi) Consultancy: Actively engaged in extending consultancy/advice for solving academic, industrial and agricultural problems (Kisan Scientific Consultancy, Latur) Research Guide Positions i) Working as Research Guide to guide Ph.D. Scholars in Microbiology since November 2002 in S.R.T.M.U., Nanded ii) Working as Research Guide in Microbiology subject in Y.C.M.O. University, Nasik since 30-09-2004 iii) Working as Research Guide in Microbiology in Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar Marathwada University, Aurangabad since 28/09/2005 iv) Working as Research Guide (Life Science) in Algappa University to guide M.Phil. Students v) Working as Research Guide (Life Science) in Periyar University, Salem to guide M.Phil. Students vi) Working as Research Guide (Life Science) in Annamalai University, Chidambaram to guide M.Phil. Students Academic Positions Held i) Secretary and Member of Board of Studies in Microbiology and Agriculture Microbiology, S.R.T.M.U., Nanded (1995 to 2000) ii) Elected as Chairman of Board of Studies in Microbiology, S.R.T.M.U., Nanded (February 03, 2001) iii) Member of Faculty of Science, S.R.T.M.U., Nanded (February 03, 2001) iv) Member of Academic Council, S.R.T.M.U., Nanded (February 03, 2001) v) Member of R.R.C., S.R.T.M.U., Nanded (February 03, 2001) and Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar University, Aurangabad (Sept., 2010) vi) Member of B.U.T.R., S.R.T.M.U., Nanded (February 03, 2001) vii) Member of Academic Council, Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar University, Aurangabad viii) Nominated as Expert by Maharashtra Govt. for inspection of Colleges willing to start Biotechnology Course ix) Member of UGC's User's Feedback Committee (April 2006), WRO Pune x) Senate and Standing Committee Member, S.R.T.M.U., Nanded from 2012 Dr. R. S. Awasthi M.Sc, Ph.D. (Microbiology) Principal COCSIT, Latur. Important Links: About RES About College Central Facility College Development Committee Institutional Development Plan College Advisery Board Local Management Committee Chairman's Message Vice Chairman's Message Principal's Message Syllabus Open Syllabus of All Courses! REV. CBCS UG COURSES (Revised CBCS) UG FY 2019-20 B.Sc (CS) - FY B.Sc (SE) - FY B.Sc (NT) - FY B.Sc (BT) - FY BCA - FY UG SY 2020-21 BCA SY B.Sc (CS) - SY B.Sc (SE) - SY B.Sc (NT) - SY UG TY 2021-22 BCA TY B.Sc. (CS) - TY B.Sc. (SE) - TY B.Sc. (NT) - TY B.Voc(SD) - FY SY TY BBA - TY B.Sc.Biotechnology - TY UG TY 2025-26 BCA TY B.Sc. (CS) - TY B.Sc. (SE) - TY B.Sc. (NT) - TY B.Sc. (CM) - TY B.Sc. (IT) - TY Note: Updated Revised CBCS Syllabus (TY) Uploaded on 13.09.2025 --> TY 2023-24 B.Sc.IT - FY SY TY B.Sc.CM - FY SY TY PG COURSES (Revised CBCS) PG FY Syllabus 2019-20 M.Sc (CS) - FY M.Sc (SE) - FY M.Sc (CM) - FY M.Sc (SAN)- FY M.Sc (BT) - FY PG SY Syllabus 2020-21 M.Sc (CS)- SY M.Sc (SE)- SY M.Sc (CM)- SY M.Sc (SAN)- SY MCA MCA PG FY & SY 